{
   "info" : "<table width=\"100%\" summary=\"page for prussian\"><tr><td>prussian</td><td style=\"text-align: right;\">R Documentation</td></tr></table>\\n<h2>Prussian army horse kick data</h2>\\n<h3>Description</h3>\\n<p>Deaths by year, by corp, from horse kicks.\\n</p>\\n<h3>Usage</h3>\\n<pre>data(prussian)</pre>\\n<h3>Format</h3>\\n<p>A data frame with 280 observations on the following 3 variables.\\n</p>\\n<dl>\\n<dt><code>y</code></dt><dd><p>a numeric vector, count of deaths</p>\\n</dd>\\n<dt><code>year</code></dt><dd><p>a numeric vector, 18XX, year of observation</p>\\n</dd>\\n<dt><code>corp</code></dt><dd><p>a <code>factor</code>, corp of Prussian Army generating\\nobservation</p>\\n</dd>\\n</dl>\\n<h3>Source</h3>\\n<p>von Bortkiewicz, L. 1898. <em>Das Gesetz der Kleinen Zahlen.</em> Leipzig: Teubner. \\n</p>\\n<h3>Examples</h3>\\n<pre>\\ndata(prussian)\\ncorpP &lt;- glm(y ~ corp, family=poisson,data=prussian)\\nsummary(corpP)\\n</pre>\\n",
